    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Defined.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** *** Standard notion of structure *)\n(** We say that [(P, H)] is a _standard notion of structure_ if this\n    preorder is in fact a partial order, for all [x : X]. *)\n\n(** A partial order is an antisymmetric preorder, i.e., we must have\n    [a <= b <= a -> a = b]. *)\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Class IsStandardNotionOfStructure X (P : NotionOfStructure X) :=\n  antisymmetry_structure : forall x (a b : P x),\n                             a <= b -> b <= a -> a = b.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** Note that for a standard notion of structure, each type [P x] must\n    actually be a set. *)\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "#[export] Instance istrunc_homomorphism_standard_notion_of_structure\n       X P `{@IsStandardNotionOfStructure X P} x\n: IsHSet (P x).",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": [
        {
          "_type": "goal",
          "name": null,
